'''Ken Wheat''' (born [[1950s#1950|1950]]) is a filmmaker. Along with his brother [[Jim Wheat]], he wrote and directed ''[[Ewoks: The Battle for Endor]]'', from a story by [[George Lucas]]. Their other credits include the 1999 telefilm [[Wikipedia:Free Fall (1999 film)|''Free Fall'']], which starred [[Hayden Christensen]].

